        // Banner
        .inner_banner.about_img
        // End Banner
        // About content
        .container
          .mt_60.mb_60
            .row
              .col-md-12
                span.reveal-title How
                h2 the Matching Algorithm Works
                .separator
                p.lead
                span.orange To find your perfect Fitness Friend, we implement a special tailor designed algorithm to find your potential matches.
                br
                | Using your information, we will cross reference you with millions of other users to present to you your top matches based on our matching criteria.
          .mt_60.mb_60
            .row
              .col-md-12
                h2 Matching Criteria
                .separator
                #accordion.accordion(role='tablist', aria-multiselectable='true')
                  .card.border-0
                    #headingOne.card-header(role='tab')
                      h5.mb-0
                        a(data-toggle='collapse', data-parent='#accordion', href='#collapseOne', aria-expanded='true', aria-controls='collapseOne')
                          | Location Based
                    #collapseOne.collapse.show(role='tabpanel', aria-labelledby='headingOne')
                      .card-block
                        | In the registration page we ask that you submit your postcode, whereas suburb input is optional.
                        | However, we also implement geotracking to pin point your location.
                        | We also ask that you input a distance (km) range of how far you are willing to travel,
                        | this is not mandatory and will default to 10km if no range is specified.
                        | Using this data, we find you your perfect match in your surrounding suburbs within the range.
                  .card.border-0
                    #headingTwo.card-header(role='tab')
                      h5.mb-0
                        a.collapsed(data-toggle='collapse', data-parent='#accordion', href='#collapseTwo', aria-expanded='false', aria-controls='collapseTwo')
                          | Fitness Level & Activity
                    #collapseTwo.collapse(role='tabpanel', aria-labelledby='headingTwo')
                      .card-block
                        | Users may select from three different fitness levels: beginner, intermediate and advanced, as well as four different fitness activities: cardio, strength, flexibility and sports.
                        | This allows for us to find you a match with the same fitness level and activity type.
                  .card.border-0
                    #headingThree2.card-header(role='tab')
                      h5.mb-0
                        a.collapsed(data-toggle='collapse', data-parent='#accordion', href='#collapseThree', aria-expanded='false', aria-controls='collapseThree')
                          | Age & Gender
                    #collapseThree.collapse(role='tabpanel', aria-labelledby='headingThree2')
                      .card-block
                        | If you have a preference for what age or gender you would like to find in a match, you can also specify this when signing up with Fitness Friends,
                        | and we will take this into consideration when generating your matches.
        // End About content
      // Footer
      footer.bg-orange.mt_150.whole-container-text-white
        | Copyright 2017 © University of Western Australia
